MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Nutrients and TOC collected quarterly. Old pilings and other hazards can be present in the shallows. Maintain at least 1.5 ft water depth and travel at slow speeds.

OrganizationFormalName: Lummi Tribe of the Lummi Reservation (Tribal)
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Nutrients and TOC sampled quarterly. Site has been known for heavy beaver activity. Samples collected from top of culvert or from left bank of channel. Be ware of fencing and barbed wire. Site also has a temperature logger present that is downloaded monthly.

OrganizationFormalName: Lummi Tribe of the Lummi Reservation (Tribal)
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: At least 1.5  feet of water is needed to cross over the shallow, often exposed beach connecting Portage Island to Gooseberry Point (the horn).  Head south around the horn and try to cut across channel in the middle of crossing at a perpendicular angle (an easterly direction) while checking visually for maximum water depth.

OrganizationFormalName: Lummi Tribe of the Lummi Reservation (Tribal)
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Samples are collected from left bank. Site also has a temperature logger that is downloaded quarterly.

OrganizationFormalName: Lummi Tribe of the Lummi Reservation (Tribal)
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Samples are collected from culvert on East side of Lummi Shore Road.  Site is sampled monthly for bacteria and other water quality parameters and quarterly for nutrients. Site also has a temperature logger present that is downloaded monthly.

OrganizationFormalName: Lummi Tribe of the Lummi Reservation (Tribal)
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Sampled from right bank approx. 10 feet upstream of boat launch ramp.  Site monitored three to four times monthly for bacteria and other water quality parameters.

OrganizationFormalName: Lummi Tribe of the Lummi Reservation (Tribal)
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This site replaced SR005 after it was added to the Surface Water Monitoring Project. Data analyzed for SW135 should also include data logged under SR005 from 2019 onward.
